description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen within Preston START team for a Community Mental Health Nurse to cover a vacancy for a 6 month period for 30 hours per week. The days of working can be arranged for the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves the specialist assessment and triage of service users referred into the service and is often the first contact with LSCFT. Following this assessment there would be referrals onto the appropriate team for in-depth support as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must have excellent communication skills, good knowledge and understanding of the various mental health needs people live with and be compassionate, supportive and organised. They must be able to work at a rapid pace and a good knowledge of local services would be useful. We are looking for candidates, who have excellent clinical skills and knowledge and a positive approach towards people living with a mental health diagnosis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to covid restrictions many of the assessments are via telephone or Attend Anywhere but at times face to face assessments are appropriate. Excellent technology skills are also required for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team is multi-disciplinary and works closely with other mental health service providers such as GPs. There are ample opportunities for professional development and regular supervision and support is in place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Elaine Watts Service Manager&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Telephone : 07956 901 376&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Email : elaine.watts@lancashirecare.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
